children.name: Rules
children.text:
A wool knit scarf the color of the sky, emblazoned with a stylized water droplet and gust of wind. 
When you move at least 30 feet in a single turn, the scarf unfurls and billows dramatically in the air as if carried by an unseen wind. In addition, the faster you move, the longer the scarf seems to become, returning to its original size at the end of your turn. 
Once per long rest, when you roll for initiative and are tied with one or more creatures, you can choose to go before them in the turn order. You cannot benefit from a Gusters scarf replica more than once per long rest.
